fontTheory.description: A typography system strictly using only the fonts extracted from the PDF: d7_f1, d7_f2, d7_f3. Following Derrida's philosophy of deconstruction, we've preserved the original typography without introducing external elements.
fontTheory.readability: The fonts chosen maintain consistency and readability within the system, ensuring a coherent visual identity.
fontTheory.hierarchy: The hierarchy is established through font sizes, weights, and styles rather than font families due to the limitation of available fonts.
fontTheory.fontPairings: Font pairings are achieved by utilizing different weights, sizes, and styles of the limited fonts to create visual distinctions between various text elements.
